<subSubSection id="C35033E6FFD0125E4485EA229026F858" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF5606DFFD0125E4485EA229026F858" blockId="46.[151,1436,1562,2028]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B93EBC7FFFD0125E4485EA22956DF940" bold="true" box="[198,326,1642,1668]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
—An endemic African genus characterized by the following combination of characters: snout sharply angular in profile, with a keratinized horizontal edge in adults, supralabial imbrication pattern T-II or T-X, nasal shield incompletely divided and lacking posterior concavity, nostrils directed ventrally, inferior nasal suture contacting first or second supralabial or rostral 
<emphasis id="B93EBC7FFFD0125E470DEAAB90ABF938" box="[846,1152,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
(
<taxonomicName id="4C4A1BEEFFD0125E4715EAAB905CF938" box="[854,1143,1763,1788]" class="Reptilia" family="Typhlopidae" genus="Megatyphlops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">Megatyphlops anomalus</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
, 3–7 postoculars, dorsal rostral broad (greater than 1/2 interocular head width), ventral rostral broad (greater than 1/2 internarial snout width), well-developed eye with discernible pupil, dorsum pigmented (often with lineate, mottled or blotched pattern), and vestigial left lung present. Other typical characters include 30–44 midbody scale rows, robust body (length/width 17–58), and large size (maximum length 
<quantity id="4CB2CD88FFD0125E4723EBCA902BF858" box="[864,1024,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="650.0" valueMax="950.0" valueMin="350.0">350–950 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35033E6FFD0125E4485EBE295C3F828" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF5606DFFD0125E4485EBE29771F800" blockId="46.[151,1436,1562,2028]" box="[198,858,1962,1988]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B93EBC7FFFD0125E4485EBE2954DF800" bold="true" box="[198,358,1962,1988]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
—Endemic to eastern and southern Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5606DFFD0125E4485EB9A95C3F828" blockId="46.[151,1436,1562,2028]" box="[198,488,2002,2028]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
